register.description: This register controls the L3INIT power state to reach upon a domain sleep transition.Note: In the L3INIT power domain OFF state is only allowed in systems where Ethernet RGMII is NOT used in the system - this is very application specific and may not be available in all TI standard software offerings.

bitfield.description: L3INIT BANK2 state when domain is ON.

bitenum.description: Memory bank is on when the domain is ON.

bitfield.description: L3INIT BANK1 state when domain is ON.

bitenum.description: Memory bank is on when the domain is ON.

bitfield.description: L3INIT BANK2 state when domain is RETENTION.

bitenum.description: Memory bank is retained when domain is in RETENTION state.

bitfield.description: L3INIT BANK1 state when domain is RETENTION.

bitenum.description: Memory bank is off when the domain is in the RETENTION state.

bitfield.description: Power state change request when domain has already performed a sleep transition. Allows going into deeper low power state without waking up the power domain.

bitenum.description: Do not request a low power state change.
Request a low power state change. This bit is automatically cleared when the power state is effectively changed or when power state is ON.

bitfield.description: Logic state when power domain is RETENTION

bitenum.description: Only retention registers are retained and remaing logic is off when the domain is in RETENTION state.
Whole logic is retained when domain is in RETENTION state.

bitfield.description: Power state control

register.description: This register provides a status on the current L3INIT power domain state. [warm reset insensitive].

bitfield.description: Last low power state entered. Set to 0x3 upon write of the same only. This register is intended for debug purpose only.

bitenum.description: Power domain was previously in RETENTION

bitfield.description: Domain transition status

bitenum.description: No on-going transition on power domain
Power domain transition is in progress.

bitfield.description: L3INIT BANK2 state status
L3INIT BANK1 state status
Logic state status
Current power state status

register.description: This register controls the release of the PCIESS local reset.

bitfield.description: PCIESS2 local reset control

bitenum.description: Reset is cleared for the PCIE2
Reset is asserted for the PCIE2

bitfield.description: PCIESS1 local reset control

bitenum.description: Reset is cleared for the PCIE1
Reset is asserted for the PCIE1

register.description: This register logs the different reset sources of the PCIESS domain. Each bit is set upon release of the domain reset signal. Must be cleared by software. [warm reset insensitive]

bitfield.description: PCIESS2 local SW reset

bitenum.description: PCIE2 has been reset upon SW reset

bitfield.description: PCIESS1 local SW reset

bitenum.description: PCIE1 has been reset upon SW reset
